## https://x.com/eienel_eth/status/2075705444639629727
api https://api.fxtwitter.com/eienel_eth/status/2075705444639629727 status 200 bytes 5619
author eienel_eth created Fri Jul 10 22:15:17 +0000 2026
text I did a full independent audit of the HFHE v2 bounty from the public artifacts.  |  | v1 fell to the R_com oracle.  | v2 deletes it and masks every value with an unseen random pad, so the only public number is T = v*R and no guess is checkable.  |  | I ran the devs' own attack suite on the real ciphertext, plus LPN, key reuse, git history, 1,200 seed hypotheses through a verified address checker, and sanitizer fuzzing. No public recovery path found. |  | @lambda0xE @octralex  would value your eyes on the analysis. Full writeup and reproducible tooling: https://eienel.github.io/hfhe-challenge-eienel/
urls ['https://eienel.github.io/hfhe-challenge-eienel/']
