text DAY 3 UPDATE (WRITTEN + RAN) |  | built + ran the timing/constancy probes on Apple Silicon |  | no sk-dependent leaks, statistically clean → DAY3 PASS |  | Built pvac on Apple Silicon (-march=armv8-a+crypto), ran real benchmarks: | prf_R: ~15.3 ms | enc_value: ~43.4 ms (2 layers / 37 edges) |  | Constancy (independent keys, 7 runs each): | skA 44.07 ms vs skB 41.90 ms → statistically equal | → no sk-dependent timing branch. No remote-relevant leak. No exploit path. |  | Status: DAY3 PASS.  | Next = Day 4–5 algebraic/reduced-params notes; |  | Day 7 freeze still stands if nothing simplifies.
